</div>
<p>
This section of the website is really to give you some basic goals and objectives to aim for in your journey of
learning Khmer.  It must be said at the outset that learning a new language is a huge undertaking, and essentially
you are going to have to learn to say and understand thousands of new words.  You are going to learn an entirely new alphabet (the biggest one in the world) and system of reading and writing.  You will learn to produce sounds that we don't have in the English language.  You will learn a different grammar system, new ways of expressing tenses, and be free from the headache of conjugating verbs.  On top of that you will be learning to speak with different levels of formality depending on the situation you find youself in, and you will have to contend with different accents from around the nation of Cambodia.  All in all you can see this is a huge mission you are setting out on! However, it is an enjoyable one, and we are going to be here to help you in any way that we can.
</p>
